      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ONEDINS CRUSADE (7) made a strong return to racing when only a head away in second at this circuit and distance. Drawn to enjoy a nice run, with luck possibly playing a role at some point. Fitter so if she gets the gaps she could be hard to hold out. ROCKET RALPH (8) has been in the placings in both starts so far this prep. Recorded a strong performance last time when he raced parked and battled on bravely for a 2.3m third at Menangle. Came from this barrier to miss narrowly when resuming here prior. Building in fitness and could break through. TRIED AND TRUSTED (10) deserved the last-start win by 4.3 metres at Newcastle after placing in the previous two outings. Tricky draw but he is racing well. TIGER EUPHEME (9) was a winner at this circuit and distance last month and could be heading towards another, improving last time out for third from a similar draw to this at Menangle.",
